Rating: 3
This was a success! However, I'd like to note that the water should be near boiling when placed in the oven, and a higher temperature was also necessary to produce a golden crust. My ramekins were slightly larger than 1 cup, so I raised the temperature to 400, and then turned the broiler on at the very end. Lastly, I reduced the fat by using 1 cup skim milk and 1/2 cup heavy cream. They turned out perfectly!

